==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Alcoholmeter
<hw>Al`co*hol"me*ter</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Alcohol</ets> + <ets>-meter</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>An instrument for determining the strength of spirits, with a scale
graduated so as to indicate the percentage of pure alcohol, either by
weight or volume. It is usually a form of hydrometer with a special
scale.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Alcoholmetrical</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Alcoholometrical</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Alcoholometric</ent>⟦br⟧
